            "answer_text": "Hmm, this is a common question to be asked by drunk guests in an ozashiki (dinner party) The answer is most likely no. The innermost layer of their clothing are strips of cloth wrapped around the waist and hip, followed by a short undergarment called hadajuban. Many geishas don\u2019t want to wear Western-style underwear, especially if they are dancers, because the elastics will show through the kimono and it looks unseemly. This isn\u2019t to be used to construct sexual innuendos about geishas, though. This used to be the common fashion of about a century ago, when most women still wore kimonos, and geishas generally follow the fashion of that age. In the context of traditional Japanese clothing, this isn\u2019t at all peculiar. ",
